body:
I am trying to get started with Kubernetes, running on Mac OS v 10.9.5, Vagrant v 1.7.4, VirtualBox v 4.3.28, and Kubernetes v 1.0.3. I've tried both the curl and the download approaches to installing, following the Vagrant getting started guide. 

No matter what I try I cannot get the installer to complete. It gets to the "Waiting for each minion to be registered with cloud provider" step then will run forever if I let it. 

I can 'vagrant ssh minion-1' and get to the server but 'kubectl get nodes' returns nothing. When I ssh into the minion and look at the logs it appears there is a cert problem. Looking at my home directory, kubernetes dir, etc. I'm not seeing where any certs were installed. 

I'm guessing this is the problem but am not sure if this is a problem with my machine infrastructure, the installer, etc.

Any help is appreciated.
